        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(plugins): apply output text transforms to toolcall_delta and toolcall_end events",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`toolcall_delta` and `toolcall_end` stream events bypass the output text replacement pipeline. When plugin `textTransforms` mask PII tokens (e.g. `\"John Smith\"` → `\"[MASKED]\"`), the LLM generates tool calls using masked tokens. Since these event types aren't processed, masked tokens leak into tool arguments and external systems.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`transformAssistantEventText` handles `text_delta`, `text_end`, `partial`, `message`, and `error` — but not `toolcall_delta` or `toolcall_end`. The `stream.result()` path also lacked tool-call argument handling.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Add `toolcall_delta` to the delta replacement path\n- Add `toolcall_end.toolCall` handling via `transformToolCallText` — transforms `arguments` recursively, **preserves `name`** (renaming tools breaks routing)\n- Add `arguments` transform to `transformContentText` for `stream.result()` / `done.message` tool-call blocks\n\nCloses #97761\n\n## Change Type\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n\n## Scope\n\n- [x] Agents (plugin text transform pipeline)\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Runtime proof** (`node --import tsx` calling real production functions):\n\n```\n=== toolcall_delta ===\ndelta: {\"query\":\"John\"}\n✅ PASS\n\n=== toolcall_end ===\nname: search (preserved ✅)\narguments: {\"query\":\"John\",\"nested\":{\"note\":\"ask John again\"},\"entries\":[\"John\",7]}\n✅ PASS — all nested args restored\n\n=== result.content (tool-call block) ===\narguments: {\"text\":\"John\"}\n✅ PASS — result path restored\n```\n\nAll three paths transform correctly: streaming deltas, terminal tool-call events, and accumulated result content blocks. Tool names are preserved to avoid breaking tool routing.\n\n## Security Impact\n\n- New permissions? No\n- Secrets handling changed? No\n- New network calls? No\n",
